Bodyids for neuron classes

Source: R/hemibrain_data.R
classed.ids.Rd

Bodyids for neuron classes. Hard saved equivalent for class2ids. However, you should use class2ids for the most up-to-date information.

An object of class data.frame with 2651 rows and 44 columns.

Details

neuPrint bodyids for neurons that the FlyConnectome groups at the University of Cambridge Department of Zoology, have determined to fall into different classes.

See also

class2ids

# \donttest{
head(rn.ids)
